stimulusHtml: Which of the following best describes the value returned by the method?

features.html:
Consider the following method. When an element of the two-dimensional array  values  is accessed, the first index is used to specify the row and the second index is used to specify the column.

 

public static int enigma(int[][] values, int x, int target)
{
   int result = 0;
   for (int num : values[x])
   {
      if (num == target)
      {
         result++;
      }
   }
   return result;
}

choicesHtml: The index of a column in  values  that contains at least one element equal to  target
The index of a row in  values  that contains at least one element equal to  target
The number of times that an element equal to  target  appears in column  x  of  values
The number of times that an element equal to  target  appears in row  x  of  values
